    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#oliverio1929"/>p. 144, n.  <citedRange>19</citedRange> (ph.)</bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>9.157</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>023000</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-64231"><name nymRef="#Θεύχρηστος">Θεύχρηστος</name>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-62830"><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Ἀμώμητος">Ἀμωμήτω</name></persName></persName>.
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Theukhrestos fils d'Amômètos.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Theuchrestos son of Amometos.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Theuchrestos figlio di Amometos.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>This base sustained a statue of the person named in the inscription. At the nominative case, the name is a caption, so that the monument is mainly honorific.
                    However, being erected in the sanctuary of Apollo, it is at least placed under the protection of the god and might also be taken as some sort of a dedication to him.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
